This is a minimal Express app with two endpoints (`/health` and `/users`) returning hard-coded data. **There are no dynamic inputs processed, no database queries, no authentication, no file system access, and no user-controllable data flowing into responses.** As a result, most of the vulnerability classes you asked about (injection, authN/authZ flaws, input validation) **do not apply to the current code** — there is no attack surface for them yet.

