### 3. No CORS policy declared (A05) — Real

No explicit CORS configuration means browser clients follow same-origin defaults, which is fine today, but any future frontend will tempt a permissive `cors()` call. Decide explicitly now:

```js
const cors = require('cors');
app.use(cors({ origin: 'https://yourdomain.example', methods: ['GET'] }));
```

### 4. PII exposure without authentication (A01: Broken Access Control) — Real, latent

`/users` returns names and email addresses with no authentication. For mock data this is harmless, but the shape of the endpoint invites adding real users later without adding auth. Put the gate in now:

