const PORT = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, HOST, () => console.log(`listening on ${HOST}:${PORT}`));
```

### 9. `/health` leaks server time and is unauthenticated (minor — OWASP A01/A05)
`timestamp: new Date().toISOString()` is low-risk but unnecessary. For liveness probes, prefer `{ status: 'ok' }` only, and if you add a `/ready` check, keep dependency details out of the public response.

