- No SQL/NoSQL/command/LDAP injection (no data-layer calls).
- No auth logic present to misuse (so no broken auth primitives to flag — but auth **is missing** where it should exist, see #3).
- No deserialization of untrusted input.
- No use of `eval`, `child_process`, dynamic `require`, or template rendering.
- No hard-coded secrets in `app.js` itself. (I did not audit `.env.test`; tell me if you want that covered.)

