### 🔴 HIGH — A05: Security Misconfiguration (no security headers)

There is no `helmet()` middleware. Express also sends `X-Powered-By: Express` by default, which aids fingerprinting.

**Recommendation:**

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.disable('x-powered-by');
app.use(helmet());
app.use(helmet.hsts({ maxAge: 31536000, includeSubDomains: true, preload: true }));
```

---

### 🟠 MEDIUM — A04: Insecure Design (no rate limiting)

Both endpoints can be hit unbounded, enabling enumeration and trivial DoS.

**Recommendation:**

