app.use(morgan('combined'));

// 404
app.use((req, res) => res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not Found' }));

// Central error handler — never leak stack traces
app.use((err, req, res, _next) => {
  console.error({ msg: 'request_error', path: req.path, err: err.message });
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' });
});
```

---

### 🟡 LOW — A05: Hardcoded port and listen address

`app.listen(3000, ...)` binds on all interfaces by default. In many deploys you want to bind to localhost and front with a reverse proxy.

```js
