const HOST = process.env.HOST || '127.0.0.1';
app.listen(PORT, HOST, () => console.log(`listening on ${HOST}:${PORT}`));
```

---

### 🟡 LOW — No body-size limits / input validation scaffolding

No routes currently take user input, but there's also no `express.json({ limit: ... })` guard or validation library wired up. Add these before you accept any POST/PUT, or a future contributor will forget.

```js
